Name: CHECK_MASS_CONSERVATION
Description: FORTRAN compile flag to enforce conservation of mass

Name: TITLE
Description: Title for run

Name: PARALLEL
Description: FORTRAN compile flag for turning on parallel computations.

Name: PX
Description: Number for parallel cores/threads to use in x direction

Name: PY
Description: Number for parallel cores/threads to use in y direction

Name: Nglob
Description: Number of points in x direction

Name: Mglob
Description: Number of points in y direction

Name: CARTESIAN
Description: FORTRAN compile flag for switch between cartesian coordinates and spherical coordinates

Name: DX
Description: Spatial resolution in the x direction

Name: DY
Description: Spatial resolution in the y direction

Name: StretchGrid
Description: Flag for using a grid varying grid point spacing.

Name: DX_FILE
Description: Path to text file of spacing between x grid points

Name: DY_FILE
Description: Path to text file of spacing between y grid points

Name: CORIOLIS_FILE
Description: Path to text file of Coriolis parameters at each grid point.

Name: Lon_West
Description: Longitude of west boundary in degrees

Name: Lat_South
Description: Latitude of south boundary in degrees.

Name: Dphi
Description: Spatial resolution in degree in the logitude direction

Name: Dtheta
Description: Spatial resolution in degree in the latitude direction

Name: RESULT_FOLDER
Description: Output path for run

Name: FIELD_IO_TYPE
Description: Output format for 2D field data

Name: U
Description: Flag for writing x direction velocities, u,to file

Name: V
Description: Flag for writing y direction velocities, v, to file

Name: ETA
Description: Flag for writing free surface height, eta, to files eta_xxxxx

Name: MASK
Description: Flag for writing wet/dry points, mask, to files mask_xxxxx

Name: DEPTH_OUT
Description: Flag for bathymetey data, dep, to file dep.out . Note: Data will include any smoothing and/or water level adjustments.

Name: OUT_NU
Description: Flag for writing breaking parameter, nu, to files nu_xxxxx

Name: MASK9
Description: Flag for writing Boussinesq/NSWE mask, mask9, to files mask9_xxxxx

Name: SourceX
Description: Flag for writing source terms in x direction to file

Name: SourceY
Description: Flag for writing source terms in y direction to file

Name: P
Description: Flag for writing momentum flux in x direction to file

Name: Q
Description: Flag for writing momentum flux in y direction to file

Name: Fx
Description: Flag for writing numerical flux, F, in x direction to file

Name: Fy
Description: Flag for writing numerical flux, F, in y direction to file

Name: Gx
Description: Flag for writing numerical flux, G, in x direction to file

Name: Gy
Description: Flag for writing numerical flux, G, in y direction to file

Name: AGE
Description: Flag for writing breaking age to files age_xxxxx.

Name: WaveHeight
Description: Flag for writing wave statistics; Hmo, Hsig, & Havg;  to file.

Name: T_INTV_mean
Description: Time interval for calculating wave statistics over.

Name: STEADY_TIME
Description: Spin up time/start time before computing wave statistics

Name: DEPTH_TYPE
Description: Bathymetry/Depth type to use.

Name: DEPTH_FILE
Description: Path to text file of still water level depth at each grid point. Note, positive values denote below water level.

Name: DEPTH_FLAT
Description: Depth of flat region in bathymetry. Note, positive values denote below water level.

Name: SLP
Description: Slope of beach

Name: Xslp
Description: x location to transition between flat depth and slope region.

Name: BATHY_CORRECTION
Description: Flag to using built in interative local smoothing scheme to bathymetry data

Name: WaterLevel
Description: Additional water level to add/substract from still water level in bathymetry data

Name: TOTAL_TIME
Description: Total simulation time for run

Name: PLOT_START_TIME
Description: Optional offset for initial start time of run

Name: PLOT_INTV
Description: Time interval between wrtiting 2D field data to file

Name: SCREEN_INTV
Description: Time interval between summary updates in log file output

Name: INI_UVZ
Description: Flag for using hot start mode. Allows specifiying initial free surface height (eta) and velocities (u, v) for run

Name: BED_DEFORMATION
Description: DEPRECATED?

Name: ETA_FILE
Description: Path to initial free surface height at grid points  to initialize run with

Name: U_FILE
Description: Optional path to initial x-direction velocities, u, at grid points  for hot start mode.

Name: V_FILE
Description: Optional path to initial y-direction velocities, v, at grid points  for hot start mode.

Name: MASK_FILE
Description: DEPRECATED?

Name: HotStartTime
Description: Optional offset for initial start time of hot start run

Name: OutputStartNumber
Description: Optional offset number for field data file output numbers in hot start run

Name: WAVEMAKER
Description: Wave maker type to use in simulation

Name: Sed_Scheme
Description: Numerical scheme for sediment transport equation

Name: PLOT_INTV_SEDIMENT
Description: Plot interval between sediment 2D field outputs

Name: CohesiveSediment
Description: Swap between coehesive (T) and non-cohesive (F) sediment

Name: D50
Description: Median grain diameter of sediment

Name: Sdensity
Description: Gravity of sediment

Name: n_porosity
Description: Porosity of sediment

Name: WS
Description: Settling velocity

Name: Shields_cr
Description: Shields parameter for suspended load

Name: Shields_cr_bedload
Description: Shields parameter for bedload based on Meyer-Peter and Muller (1984)

Name: Kappa1
Description: Runge-Kutta parameter kappa1 for sediment transport solver

Name: Kappp2
Description: Runge-Kutta parameter kappa2 for sediment transport solver

Name: MinDepthPickup
Description: The minimum depth for sediment pickup action. The purpose of this parameter is to avoid over-shooting at a very small depth

Name: k_coh
Description: Diffusion coefficien

Name: Tau_cr_coh
Description: Critical shear stress for erosion

Name: Tau_crd_coh
Description: Critical shear stress for deposition

Name: a_coh
Description: Empirical parameter used to calculate settling velocity.

Name: b_coh
Description: Empirical parameter used to calculate settling velocity.

Name: n_coh
Description: Empirical parameter used to calculate settling velocity.

Name: m_coh
Description: Empirical parameter used to calculate settling velocity.

Name: E_coh
Description: Erodibility parameter

Name: alpha_coh
Description: Coefficient used to calculate the erosion rate for soft bed

Name: Bed_Change
Description: Update bathymetry based on sediment transport

Name: Hard_bottom
Description: Turns on/off erosion

Name: Hard_bottom_file
Description: Path to text file containing thickiness in meters of erodible bed at each grid point

Name: Morph_step
Description: Ratio of Boussinesq model time steps to the morphological updating step

Name: Avalanche
Description: Turns on/off avalanche calculations

Name: Tan_phi
Description: Tangent of the repose angle
